org.codefx.libfx.collection.transform

Class TransformingMapBuilder<IK,OK,IV,OV>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.codefx.libfx.collection.transform.TransformingMapBuilder<IK,OK,IV,OV>
  • Type Parameters:
    IK - the inner key type of the created transforming map, i.e. the type of the keys contained in the wrapped/inner map
    OK - the outer key type of the created transforming map, i.e. the type of keys appearing to be in this map
    IV - the inner value type of the created transforming map, i.e. the type of the values contained in the wrapped/inner map
    OV - the outer value type of the created transforming map, i.e. the type of values appearing to be in this map

    public class TransformingMapBuilder<IK,OK,IV,OV>
extends Object
    Builder for TransformingMaps.

    A builder can be obtained by calling forTypes or forTypesUnknown(). The building method TODO can only be called after transformations from inner to outer keys and values and vice versa have been set.

      • forTypesUnknown

        public static <IK,OK,IV,OV> TransformingMapBuilder<IK,OK,IV,OV> forTypesUnknown()
        Returns a new builder for unknown inner and outer key and value types.

        This is equivalent to calling forTypes(Object.class, Object.class, Object.class, Object.class). To obtain a builder for <IK, OK, IV, OV> you will have to call TransformingMapBuilder.<IK, OK, IV, OV> forTypesUnknown().

        Type Parameters:
        IK - the inner key type of the created transforming map, i.e. the type of the keys contained in the wrapped/inner map
        OK - the outer key type of the created transforming map, i.e. the type of keys appearing to be in this map
        IV - the inner value type of the created transforming map, i.e. the type of the values contained in the wrapped/inner map
        OV - the outer value type of the created transforming map, i.e. the type of values appearing to be in this map
        Returns:
        a new builder
